aud using a risk management approach. It outlines various strategies that can be easily implemented to help prevent identity theft and fraud. It addresses technical issues in a clear and uncomplicated way to help decision-makers at all levels understand the steps their businesses and organizations can take to mitigate identity theft and fraud risks. And it highlights the risks individuals face in this digital age. This book can help anyone – businesses and organizations of all sizes, as well as individuals – develop an identity theft and fraud prevention strategy that will reduce their risk and protect their identity assets. To date, little has been written on identity theft and fraud with a Canadian audience in mind. This book fills that gap, helping Canadians minimize their identity theft and fraud risks.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aFraud -- Canada. 0aGuinane, Basil. 0aHeart -- Diseases -- Diet therapy -- Recipes. 0aHeart -- Diseases -- Patients -- Biography. 0aHeart -- Diseases -- Patients -- Family relationships. 0aIdentity theft -- Canada -- Prevention. 0aIdentity theft -- Canada. 0aIdentity theft -- Prevention. 0aLow-cholesterol diet -- Recipes. 0aRoss, Cecily. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Insurance / Risk Assessment & Management.2bisacsh1 aSproule, Susan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aXiang, Junlian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aYuan, Yufei, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012z978311127413308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012z978311127716540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780776619927423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780776619927/original  a978-3-11